1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,131
You often hear that certain jobs require considerable physical maturity, jobs like selling securities and insurance.

2
00:00:08,401 --> 00:00:16,210
That you've got to have either gray hair or no hair at all in order to gain an investor's confidence is plain nonsense.

3
00:00:16,401 --> 00:00:19,730
What really matters is how well you know your job.

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,330
If you know your job and understand people, you're sufficiently mature to handle it.

5
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:34,611
Age has no real relation to ability, unless you convince yourself that years alone will give you the stuff you need to make your mark.

6
00:00:35,361 --> 00:00:39,971
Many young people feel that they are being held back because of their youth.

7
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:48,691
Now, it is true that another person in an organization who is insecure and job-scared may try to block your way forward,

8
00:00:48,881 --> 00:00:51,250
using age or some other reason.

9
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:55,250
But the people who really count in the company will not.

10
00:00:55,441 --> 00:01:00,131
They will give you as much responsibility as they feel you can handle well.

11
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:07,571
Demonstrate that you have ability and positive attitudes, and your youthfulness will be considered an advantage.

12
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:16,691
In quick recap, the cure for age excusitis is, number one, look at your present age positively.

13
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:21,330
Think, I'm still young, not I'm already old.

14
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:27,651
Practice looking forward to new horizons and gain the enthusiasm and the feel of youth.

15
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:32,931
Number two, compute how much productive time you have left.

16
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:39,171
Remember, a person age 30 still has 80% of his productive life ahead of him.

17
00:01:39,361 --> 00:01:46,770
And the 50-year-old still has a big 40%, the best 40%, of his opportunity years left.

18
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:50,691
Life is actually longer than most people think.

19
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:56,370
Three, invest future time in doing what you really want to do.

20
00:01:56,960 --> 00:02:01,651
It's too late only when you let your mind go negative and think it's too late.

21
00:02:01,921 --> 00:02:05,250
Stop thinking, I should have started years ago.

22
00:02:05,441 --> 00:02:07,171
That's failure thinking.

23
00:02:07,441 --> 00:02:10,370
Instead think, I'm going to start now.

24
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,691
My best years are ahead of me.

25
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:15,730
That's the way successful people think.

